1. Dice the tomato:

Wash, peel and cut the carrot into small pieces. Peel and chop the onion. Chop the tomato in small pieces.

2. Cook the carrot:

Boil water in a pot and cook the onion for 5-6 minutes. Drain and put away.

3. Boil the eggs and let them cool:

Fill a pot with salted water, when the water starts to boil, add the eggs, being careful not to break them (you can help yourself with a spoon). Boil for 10 minutes. After the cooking time, transfer them to a container with cold water to stop the cooking and be able to peel them easily.

4. peel and cut the eggs:

Carefully remove the shells. Run them under tap water to remove impurities from the shells. Cut off the top of each egg.

5. Mix the yolks and the carrot:

Scoop out the yolks with a coffee spoon and be very careful not to break the whites. Mix the yolks with the cooked carrot.

6. Add the tuna:

In a large bowl put the tuna, with the onion and tomato. Add the yolk mixture, garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.

7. Fill the whites:

Shred it all. It doesn't have to be too fine a grind. Fill the hollow egg whites with this mixture that you have crushed.

8. Serve with chives:

Wash and cut the chives into very small pieces. Sprinkle over each egg and serve. If you are not going to serve them right away, store them in the fridge.
